The beginning of the forecast period of national security of the period of independence of Azerbaijan is considered to the signing of the cease-fire agreement on 14 October 1991. It was a result of Azerbaijan's readiness to abide by the terms of the cease-fire. The Constitution of the Azerbaijan Republic has been revised to be compatible with the general approach set forth in international law and the European system of human rights. The Parliament of the Azerbaijan Republic have adopted a number of international treaties and emphasised security issues. The process of building a democratic nation also began. At the same time, in that period, the Azerbaijan Republic have sought to eliminate the lasting consequence of the events taking place in connection with the Russia crisis: products have been gradually withdrawn from the market of communication items, military units were reorganized into individual units. At the same time, the integration of national security mechanisms is gradually becoming reality.
